    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="text-sm italic mb-8">Last Updated: December 22, 2025</p>

    <div class="space-y-6 text-sm">
      <p>Crate Crawler ("we," "us," or "our") is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we handle your information when you use our website and YouTube playlist creation services.</p>

      <section>
        <h2 class="font-bold text-lg">1. Information We Collect</h2>
        <p><strong>Email Address:</strong> We collect the email address you provide in our form to send you a confirmation link once your playlist has been successfully created.</p>
        <p><strong>YouTube Data:</strong> We use Google OAuth to request access to your YouTube account. Our application specifically uses the <code>youtube.force-ssl</code> (or <code>playlist.modify</code>) scope.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="font-bold text-lg">2. How We Use Your Data</h2>
        <p>We use the YouTube API to:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc ml-5">
          <li>Create a new, private or unlisted playlist on your YouTube account.</li>
          <li>Search for and add tracks based on the Discogs URL you provided.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-2">We do not access, read, or delete your existing playlists, search history, or personal YouTube data.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="font-bold text-lg">3. Data Retention and Security</h2>
        <ul class="list-disc ml-5">
          <li><strong>No Permanent Storage:</strong> We do not store your YouTube access tokens or Discogs data after your request is processed.</li>
          <li><strong>Authentication:</strong> We never see or store your Google password. Authentication is handled entirely by Google’s secure servers.</li>
          <li><strong>Third-Party Disclosure:</strong> We do not sell, trade, or otherwise transfer your personal information to outside parties.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="font-bold text-lg">4. Third-Party Links and Terms</h2>
        <p>Our service relies on YouTube API Services. By using Crate Crawler, you are agreeing to be bound by the following:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc ml-5">
          <li><a href="https://www.youtube.com/t/terms" class="underline">YouTube Terms of Service</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" class="underline">Google Privacy Policy</a></li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="font-bold text-lg">5. Revoking Access</h2>
        <p>You may revoke Crate Crawler’s access to your data at any time via the <a href="https://myaccount.google.com/permissions" class="underline">Google Security Settings page</a>.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="font-bold text-lg">6. Contact Us</h2>
        <p>If you have any questions, contact us at: <strong>cratecrawler.com@gmail.com</strong></p>
      </section>
